Each [[judge]] or [[courtroom]] will{{Citation needed|date=November 2010}} have a '''law and motion calendar''', setting aside the times when only motions and special legal arguments are heard.  These items consist of pretrial motions (such as a [[motion to compel]] relating to discovery requests) or other legal requests that are not connected to a [[trial]], and do not include trials themselves.

